COLS(1): columnate words
.LP
.br
\l'5i'
.br
.LP
.SH
USAGE
.LP
.LP
\fC
.DS L

    usage: cols [-Du] [-n ncols] [-w wid] {file}
        -D: debug
        -n ncols: set number of columns
        -u: use unix output
        -w wid: set max line width
    
.DE
\fR
.LP
.LP
.SH
DESCRIPTION
.LP
\fI Cols\fR columnates words writing one row at a time. First words go
in the first row, then the second row and so on. Total text width is determined
by using the underlying OS tty size, by default.
.LP
.SH
EXAMPLE
.LP
list files in columns:
.LP
\fC
.DS L

    ; lf ,1 | cols -u
    
.DE
\fR
.LP
.LP
.SH
SOURCE
.LP
.IP \(bu
\fC/zx/sys/src/clive/cmd/cols\fR
